                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d683">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.24/132a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-22T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 22, 1941—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>108. On March 17 the Department issued licenses for the export to Greece of the
                    following arms and ammunition released under the provisions of the Act of March
                    11, 1941:<note n="93" xml:id="d683fn93">Lend-Lease Act; 55 Stat. 31.</note>
                    Fifty 75-millimeter guns, 150,000 <pb facs="0715" n="703" xml:id="pg_703"/>
                    shells for these guns, and 30,000 shells for 155-millimeter howitzers.<note
                        n="94" xml:id="d683fn94">The foregoing material was from ordnance stock
                        transferred by the War Department to the Greek Government by direction of
                        the President.</note> The appropriate authorities of this Government are now
                    considering carefully what further arms and other materials can be released for
                    export to Greece under the authority of this law. You may so inform the Greek
                    Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
